'''Alexander Sørloth''' (born 5 December 1995) is a Norwegian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].

Sørloth started his career at [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]], before spending a loan period at [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] in 2015. Following this, he transferred to [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] in the Netherlands and then to [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in Denmark. In 2018, he joined [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] in England, followed by loan spells at [[KAA Gent|Gent]] in Belgium and [[Trabzonspor]] in Turkey. He moved to [[RB Leipzig]] in Germany in 2020 and later spent two seasons on loan at [[Real Sociedad]] in Spain. In 2023, he joined [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]], before transferring to Atlético Madrid in 2024.

==Club career==
===Rosenborg===
[[File:Alexander Sørloth.JPG|thumb|upright|left|Sørloth with Rosenborg in 2013]]
After many years in the youth system Sørloth was rewarded with a contract by Rosenborg in July 2013. He played his first professional game for Rosenborg when he was subbed on in the second half of the [[2013-14 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] first qualifying round game versus [[Crusaders FC|Crusaders]], and it took him only 12 minutes to score his first goal, Rosenborg's 6th in their 7–2 win.

He made his debut in the [[Tippeligaen]] on 20 July 2014 in Rosenborg's home game against [[Sogndal Fotball|Sogndal]] coming on as a substitute for [[Alexander Søderlund]] after 60 minutes.<ref name=RefA>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftenbladet.no/100Sport/fotball/eliteserien/Debutant-Sorloth---Jeg-burde-kanskje-hatt-en-scoring-448821_1.snd|title=Debutant Sørloth: – Jeg burde kanskje hatt en scoring|access-date=1 February 2018|url-access=subscription|language=no|archive-date=4 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304053759/http://www.aftenbladet.no/100Sport/fotball/eliteserien/Debutant-Sorloth---Jeg-burde-kanskje-hatt-en-scoring-448821_1.snd|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Sørloth went on a loan to [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] before the start of the 2015 Tippeligaen. In the league he scored 13 goals and making five assist in his 26 appearances (19 starters), including scoring six goals in one game against [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]].<ref name=RefA/> In his last match for Bodø/Glimt, he scored his second hat-trick of the season, against Stabæk.

===Groningen===
On 6 November 2015, Sørloth confirmed that he would be joining [[Eredivisie]] club [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] on a 4.5-year contract at the end of the season. Groningen paid a transfer fee of around €750,000.{{Citation needed|date=April 2024}}

===Midtjylland===
On 1 June 2017, [[Danish Superliga]] club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] announced that they had signed Sørloth on a four-year contract for what the club called a 'modest fee'.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcm.dk/nyheder/fcm-tv/--vi-faar-endnu-en-klasseangriber|title=- Vi får endnu en klasseangriber|website=www.fcm.dk|access-date=1 February 2018|archive-date=10 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810215032/https://www.fcm.dk/nyheder/fcm-tv/--vi-faar-endnu-en-klasseangriber|language=da|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=dr /> In September 2017 he was named the Superliga Player of the Month.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.superliga.dk/maanedens-spiller |title=Månedens spiller - 2017-18 |publisher=superliga.dk |access-date=13 August 2018 |archive-date=13 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813210433/http://www.superliga.dk/maanedens-spiller |url-status=dead |language=da}}</ref>

===Crystal Palace===
On 31 January 2018, Sørloth signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] for a reported fee of £9&nbsp;million.<ref name="CPannounce">{{cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2018/february/sorloth-is-new-eagles-number-nine/|title=Sørloth Is New Eagles Number Nine|publisher=Crystal Palace F.C.|access-date=1 February 2018|archive-date=1 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180201060816/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2018/february/sorloth-is-new-eagles-number-nine/|url-status=live}}</ref> This made him the most expensive sale out of the Danish Superliga at the time.<ref name=dr >{{cite news| url = https://www.dr.dk/sporten/fodbold/fc-midtjylland-spraenger-rammerne-saelger-topscorer-rekorddyrt | title = FC Midtjylland sprænger rammerne: Sælger topscorer rekorddyrt | publisher = [[Danmarks Radio]] | agency = Ritzau | date = 1 February 2018|language=da }}</ref> He made his debut on 10 February 2018 in a 3–1 away defeat to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sørloth Not Satisfied After Debut |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2018/february/sorloth-not-satisfied-after-debut/ |publisher=Crystal Palace F.C. |access-date=3 June 2018 |date=10 February 2018 |archive-date=30 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830174255/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2018/february/sorloth-not-satisfied-after-debut/ |url-status=live }}</ref> At the time of the transfer, he was the top scorer in the Superliga,<ref name=dr /> and would go on to win the title at the end of the season. On 28 August, Sørloth scored his first and only goal for Palace in a 1–0 win over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] in the [[2018–19 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Alex|last=Bywater|title=Alexander Sorloth fires first Crystal Palace goal to see off Swansea in Carabao Cup|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/08/28/alexander-sorloth-fires-first-crystal-palace-goal-see-swansea/|website=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=28 August 2018|access-date=1 December 2018|archive-date=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830174148/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/08/28/alexander-sorloth-fires-first-crystal-palace-goal-see-swansea/|url-status=live}}</ref>

====Loan to Gent====
On 8 January 2019, Sørloth signed for [[Belgian Pro League|Belgian First Division A]] side [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]] on loan until the end of the 2018–19 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/alexander-sorloth-to-join-kaa-gent-for-a-season-long-loan/|title=Alexander Sørloth Joins KAA Gent on Loan|website=Crystal Palace F.C.|date=8 January 2019|access-date=8 January 2019|archive-date=9 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109110703/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/alexander-sorloth-to-join-kaa-gent-for-a-season-long-loan/|url-status=live}}</ref>

====Loan to Trabzonspor====
In August 2019, Sørloth signed for Turkish [[Süper Lig]] club [[Trabzonspor]] on loan until the end of the 2019–20 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2019/august/alexander-sorloth-joins-trabzonspor-on-loan2/|title=Alexander Sørloth joins Trabzonspor on loan|website=Crystal Palace F.C.|date=4 August 2019|access-date=4 August 2019|archive-date=9 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109110703/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/alexander-sorloth-to-join-kaa-gent-for-a-season-long-loan/|url-status=live}}</ref> He debuted for the club on 8 August against [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] in the third qualifying round of the [[2019–20 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]], where he scored the second goal in a match that ended 2–2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/trabzonspor-sonradan-acildi-1526116|title=Trabzonspor sonradan açıldı|website=www.cumhuriyet.com.tr|date=8 August 2019|language=tr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302152713/http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/trabzonspor-sonradan-acildi-1526116|url-status=live}}</ref>

In March 2020, Sørloth scored his first hat-trick for Trabzonspor in a 6–0 victory against [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasimpasa]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanatik.com.tr/sorlothtan-trabzonsporda-ilk-hat-trick-2116487|title=Sörloth'tan Trabzonspor'da ilk hat-trick|website=Fanatik|date=2 March 2020|language=tr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302152712/https://www.fanatik.com.tr/sorlothtan-trabzonsporda-ilk-hat-trick-2116487|url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 July 2020, Sørloth became Trabzonspor's top-scoring foreign player in a single season, with 29 goals, exceeding the tally of Georgian former center-forward [[Shota Arveladze]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/sorloth-makes-history-as-trabzonspor-defeats-galatasaray|title=Sorloth makes history as Trabzonspor defeats Galatasaray|website=Daily Sabah|date=6 July 2020|access-date=6 July 2020|archive-date=6 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706195145/https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/sorloth-makes-history-as-trabzonspor-defeats-galatasaray|url-status=live}}</ref>

===RB Leipzig===
[[File:Alexander Sørloth for RB Leipzig in 2022 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Sørloth lining up for [[RB Leipzig]] in 2022]]
After playing for his national team in the first two group matches of the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B#Group 1|UEFA Nations League]], Sørloth failed to return to [[Trabzon]] prior to Trabzonspor's [[2020-21 Trabzonspor season#Süper Lig|upcoming league fixture]] against [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.trabzonspor.org.tr/tr/haberler/guncel-haberler/alexander-sorloth-ile-ilgili-aciklama-12-9-2020|title=Alexander Sorloth ile ilgili açıklama|publisher=Trabzonspor|date=12 September 2020|access-date=22 September 2020|archive-date=2 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002004136/https://www.trabzonspor.org.tr/tr/haberler/guncel-haberler/alexander-sorloth-ile-ilgili-aciklama-12-9-2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 22 September 2020, Sørloth signed for [[RB Leipzig]] for an initial fee of €20&nbsp;million plus €2&nbsp;million in potential add-ons, with any proceeds to be shared evenly between Trabzonspor and Crystal Palace.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kap.org.tr/en/Bildirim/876155|title=Alexander Sorloth Transferi Hakkında|website=Kamuyu Aydınlatma Platformu|date=22 September 2020|access-date=22 September 2020|archive-date=4 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230104044416/https://www.kap.org.tr/en/Bildirim/876155|url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 December 2020, he scored the game-winning goal against [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] in a 4–3 win in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=RB Leipzig vs. Istanbul Basaksehir score: German side wins seven-goal thriller|url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/rb-leipzig-vs-istanbul-basaksehir-score-german-side-wins-seven-goal-thriller/|website=CBS Sports|date=2 December 2020 |access-date=2 December 2020|archive-date=29 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129163908/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/rb-leipzig-vs-istanbul-basaksehir-score-german-side-wins-seven-goal-thriller/|url-status=live}}</ref> which was his first goal for the club.

====Loan to Real Sociedad====
On 25 August 2021, Sørloth moved to [[La Liga]] side [[Real Sociedad]] on a [[2021–22 La Liga|season]]-long loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/en/news/details/agreement-over-the-transfer-of-alexander-sorloth|title=Agreement over the transfer of Alexander Sorloth|publisher=Real Sociedad|date=25 August 2021|accessdate=26 August 2021|archive-date=6 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221206170958/https://www.realsociedad.eus/en/news/details/agreement-over-the-transfer-of-alexander-sorloth|url-status=live}}</ref> On 29 August 2022, he returned to the ''Txuri-urdin'' on loan for another year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vuelve|trans-title=He returns|url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/es/noticias/detalle/vuelve|publisher=Real Sociedad|language=es|date=29 August 2022|accessdate=29 August 2022|archive-date=20 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230320084307/https://www.realsociedad.eus/es/noticias/detalle/vuelve|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Villarreal===
On 25 July 2023, La Liga club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] announced the signing of Sørloth on a five-year deal,<ref>{{cite web |title=Viking blood for Villarreal's attack |url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/viking-blood-for-villarreals-attack/ |publisher=Villarreal CF |date=25 July 2023 |access-date=25 July 2023 |archive-date=25 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230725194837/https://villarrealcf.es/en/viking-blood-for-villarreals-attack/ |url-status=live }}</ref> for a reported fee of €10&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|date=25 July 2023|title=Villarreal capture Alexander Sorloth|url=https://footballtoday.com/2023/07/25/villarreal-capture-alexander-sorloth/|website=Football Today|access-date=21 April 2024|archive-date=27 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927125625/https://footballtoday.com/2023/07/25/villarreal-capture-alexander-sorloth/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 27 August, he scored his first goal for the club in a 4–3 loss to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Thomas |first=Marissa |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66635282 |title=Villarreal 3–4 Barcelona |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 August 2023 |access-date=13 May 2024 |archive-date=13 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240513161103/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66635282 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 May 2024, he scored four goals in a 4–4 draw in a league game against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], reaching his 23rd goal, without penalty kicks, of the [[2023–24 La Liga|2023–24 season]] as La Liga's top scorer with one match remaining.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles/villarreal-4-4-real-madrid-laligas-top-scorer-sorloth-scores-four-in-thrilling-comeback-2024-05-19 |title=Villarreal 4–4 Real Madrid: LaLiga's top scorer Sorloth scores four in thrilling comeback |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=19 May 2024 |access-date=19 May 2024 |archive-date=20 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240520161217/https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles/villarreal-4-4-real-madrid-laligas-top-scorer-sorloth-scores-four-in-thrilling-comeback-2024-05-19 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was eventually surpassed by just one goal by [[Artem Dovbyk]], who scored a hat-trick on the final matchday of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2024/05/25/final-day-hat-trick-has-gironas-artem-dovbyk-in-pole-position-in-pichichi-trophy-showdown |title=Final day hat-trick has Girona's Artem Dovbyk in pole position in Pichichi Trophy showdown |publisher=Football España |date=25 May 2024 }}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
On 3 August 2024, Sørloth transferred to fellow La Liga club [[Atlético Madrid]] for a fee in the region of €32&nbsp;million. He signed a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |title=Welcome, Alexander Sørloth! |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/welcome-alexander-s-rloth |access-date=3 August 2024 |work=Atlético Madrid |date=3 August 2024}}</ref> A few weeks later, on 19 August, he scored his first goal on his debut in a 2–2 away draw against his former club Villarreal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/football/report/_/gameId/704669 |title=Villarreal hold Atletico Madrid to a draw in first game of season |publisher=ESPN |date=19 August 2024 }}</ref> Later that year, on 21 December, he netted a stoppage-time goal in a 2–1 victory over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], securing his club's first away win over the latter since February 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles/atletico-madrid-not-getting-carried-away-after-moving-top-of-laliga-2024-12-21 |title=Atletico Madrid not getting carried away after moving top of LaLiga |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=22 December 2024 }}</ref>

On 10 May 2025, Sørloth scored a first-half quadruple against his former club, Real Sociedad, including a [[hat-trick]] within four minutes, breaking the previous record held by [[David Villa]] in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |last=Menzies |first=John |date=10 May 2025 |title=Atletico Madrid star breaks La Liga record that stood for 19 years |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2025/05/10/atletico-madrid-sorloth-la-liga-record |publisher=Football España}}</ref> In addition, he became the first player in La Liga history to achieve a hat-trick before the 12th minute, adding a fourth goal in the 30th minute.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Alexander Sorloth inscrit un quadruplé, dont un triplé en 4 minutes avec l'Atlético face à la Real Sociedad |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Alexander-sorloth-inscrit-un-triple-en-4-minutes-avec-l-atletico-face-a-la-real-sociedad/1560724 |access-date=10 May 2025 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=SUÁREZ |first=ISAAC |date=10 May 2025 |title=Sorloth, 'hat-trick' ¡en cuatro minutos! y un póker en media hora de locura |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/atletico/2025/05/10/sorloth-hat-trick-cuatro-minutos-poker-media-hora-locura.html |access-date=10 May 2025 |website=MARCA |language=es}}</ref> He concluded his debut season with 20 goals, finishing as his club's top scorer in La Liga.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/la-liga-top-scorers-2024-25/bltbd524ffd030cff7b#cs2b32b907ef90c937 |title=La Liga top scorers 2024-25: Kylian Mbappe wins the Pichichi trophy |publisher=Goal.com |date=26 May 2025 }}</ref>

On 24 February 2026, he scored his first [[List of UEFA Champions League hat-tricks|Champions League hat-trick]] in a 4–1 win over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]], securing his club's qualification to the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|round of 16]].<ref>{{cite web |last=MacDonald |first=Keifer |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cdxzkljkjxkt |title=Atletico Madrid 4–1 Club Brugge |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 February 2026 }}</ref> On 8 April 2026, he scored the club’s second goal in a 2–0 win against  Barcelona in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League#quarter-finals|Champions League quarter-finals]].

==International career==
Sørloth debuted for the [[Norway national football team|Norwegian senior squad]] against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on 29 May 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Odd Inge|last=Aas|title=Høgmo slapp ikke til spilleren "alle" ville se|url=https://www.aftenbladet.no/sport/i/ka4dw9/hoegmo-slapp-ikke-til-spilleren-alle-ville-se|website=[[Stavanger Aftenblad]]|date=29 May 2016|language=no|quote=Mot det fjerde best rangerte laget i Europa slapp landslagssjefen til hele fem debutanter. Anders Trondsen og Veton Berisha fra start, Iver Fossum, Alexander Sørloth og Niklas Gunnarsson fra benken.|trans-quote=Against the fourth best-ranked team in Europe, national team manager [Per-Mathias Høgmo] introduced five debutants. Anders Trondsen and Veton Berisha from the start; Iver Fossum, Alexander Sørloth, and Niklas Gunnarsson from the bench.|access-date=21 April 2024|archive-date=21 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240421111101/https://www.aftenbladet.no/sport/i/ka4dw9/hoegmo-slapp-ikke-til-spilleren-alle-ville-se|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goal against Iceland the same year on 1 June.<ref>{{Cite news|first1=Bjørn S.|last1=Delebekk|first2=Jonas|last2=Wikborg|first3=Bjørn Arne|last3=Johannessen|title=Pappa Sørloth om sønnens første Norge-scoring: – Starten på noe større|trans-title=Father Sørloth on his son's first Norway goal: – The start of something bigger|url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/wWqAM/pappa-soerloth-om-soennens-foerste-norge-scoring-starten-paa-noe-stoerre|website=[[Verdens Gang]]|date=1 June 2016|language=no|access-date=21 April 2024|archive-date=21 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240421111101/https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/wWqAM/pappa-soerloth-om-soennens-foerste-norge-scoring-starten-paa-noe-stoerre|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Sørloth is the son of former [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]] player and Norwegian international [[Gøran Sørloth]].<ref name="CPannounce"/>

On 31 May 2021, an [[Instagram]] post of his surpassed 3.5&nbsp;million comments, making it the most commented post on Instagram by an athlete. It was mainly fans of the Turkish football club Trabzonspor, asking the player to return to his former loan club.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Alexander Sorloth Pleads With Trabzonspor Fans To Stop Sending Him Messages After 3.2 Million People Comment On His Post|url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/news-reactions-alexander-sorloth-asks-trabzonspor-fans-to-stop-sending-him-messages-20210603|website=Sport Bible|date=3 June 2021|access-date=2 August 2023|archive-date=2 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230802091232/https://www.sportbible.com/football/news-reactions-alexander-sorloth-asks-trabzonspor-fans-to-stop-sending-him-messages-20210603|url-status=live}}</ref>

